The makeR 3D printers are compatible with [[polylactic acid]] (PLA), [[acrylonitrile butadiene styrene]] (ABS), [[thermoplastic polyurethane]] (TPU), [[Polystyrene#Copolymers|high-impact polystyrene]] (HIPS), [[Polyvinyl acetate|polyvinyl alcohol]] (PVA) and some specials materials for industrial needs, such as PLA filament mixed with particles of metals which through sanding 3D printed parts provide appearance similar to metals ([[steel]], [[copper]], and [[aluminium]]). Also, makeR printers print with [[Nylon|nylon]] and [[Carbon fiber reinforced polymer|carbon fiber]].<ref>{{cite web |title =Meet PEGASUS 3D Printer|url=https://somosmaker.com/pegasus/|accessdate=2017-02-09|publisher=[[3D makeR Technologies S.A.S.]]|language=Spanish}}</ref>
