'''Günter Figal''' (born July 15, 1949) is a German [[philosopher]] and professor of philosophy at [[University of Freiburg]]. He is a specialist in the thought of [[Hans-Georg Gadamer]], and [[Martin Heidegger]]. His research focuses on [[hermeneutics]], [[Phenomenology (philosophy)|phenomenology]], German classical philosophy and the history of [[metaphysics]]. Figal was the president of the [[Martin-Heidegger-Society]] between 2003 and 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last1=W|first1=Justin|title=Germany's Heidegger Society Chair Resigns (updated)|url=http://dailynous.com/2015/01/19/germanys-heidegger-society-chair-resigns/|website=Daily Nous|accessdate=6 June 2017|date=19 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Interview with Günter Figal {{!}} Figure/Ground|url=http://figureground.org/interview-with-gunter-figal/|website=figureground.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Freiburg will not replace Günter Figal in the ‘Heidegger’ Chair|url=https://progressivegeographies.com/2015/03/05/freiburg-will-not-replace-gunter-figal-in-the-heidegger-chair-at-freiburg/|website=Progressive Geographies|accessdate=6 June 2017|date=5 March 2015}}</ref>
